- High-performance teams are those that have a high win-loss percentage and net rating; 
- A high win-loss percentage indicates a team has a higher number of wins compared to losses; 
- A high net rating is a measure of a team's performance, with a higher rating indicating better performance; 
- Top players are those who score a high number of points per game; 
- Recent transactions refer to player movements between teams that have occurred recently.
